<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIONS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, OCTOBER 13
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Tuesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-CIA-DRUGS-NICARAGUA (moved Saturday, Oct. 10)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Saturday, October
10, about a newly declassified report that says the Central
Intelligence Agency repeatedly ignored allegations of drug
trafficking by the anti-Sandinista rebels in Nicaragua in the
1980's, or failed to investigate, referred incorrectly in some
editions to the Acting Director of Central Intelligence in April
1987. He was Robert M. Gates, not William.
</P>
<P>
   BC-OBIT-EVANS--NYT (moved Monday, Oct. 12)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, October
12, an obituary about David C. Evans, a pioneer in computer
graphics, misstated his position in the computer science department
at the University of California at Berkeley in the 1960's. He was a
member of the department, not chairman.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CARDINAL-ALLEGIANCE-NYT (moved Saturday, Oct. 10)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Saturday, October
10, about the acquisition of the Allegiance Corporation by Cardinal
Health Inc. misstated the year in which the lower value of the
Malaysian currency, the ringgit, contributed to Allegiance's
profits. It was this year, not 1997.
</P>
</TEXT>
