<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL;  PA Contract Awards States News Service Washington, October 13
-- Westinghouse Science &AMP; Technology Center of Pittsburgh won a
$2.2 million contract from the Dept. of Energy in Pittsburgh for
research and development.
</P>
<P>
   North Central Mechanical Inc. of Bradford won a $1.9 million
contract from the Dept. of Veterans Affairs in Butler for property
maintenance and repair.
</P>
<P>
   Tri-State Design Construction Inc. of Elkins Park won a $827,000
contract from the VA Medical Center in Decatur, Ga., for property
maintenance and repair.
</P>
<P>
   Sechan Electronics Inc. of Litiz won a $339,198 contract from
the Army in Rock Island, Ill., for weapons.
</P>
<P>
   United Terex Inc. of Fairview Village won a $674,292 contract
from the Fleet and Industrial Supply Center in Bremerton, Wash.,
for ammunition and explosives.
</P>
<P>
   Boeing Defense and Space Group of Philadelphia won a $273,826
contract from the Army at the Redstone Arsenal in Alabama for
aircraft components.
</P>
<P>
   Boeing Defense and Space Group of Philadelphia won a $104,233
contract from the Army at the Redstone Arsenal in Alabama for
aircraft components.
</P>
<P>
   SPS Technologies Inc. of Jenkintown won a $68,644 contract from
the Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for engine
components.
</P>
<P>
   Penn Detroit Diesel Inc. of York Haven won a $99,685 contract
from the Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for engine
accessories.
</P>
<P>
   Triumph Controls Inc. of North Wales won a $68,899 contract from
the Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for wire rope.
</P>
<P>
   Cooper Herbert Co. Inc. of Genessee won a $63,120 contract from
the Defense Supply Center in Columbus, Ohio, for hoses.
</P>
<P>
   Leica Microsystems Inc. of Exton won a $499,880 contract from
the Dept. of Veterans Affairs in Hines, Ill., for microscopes.
</P>
<P>
   The Environmental Defense Corp. of Upper Darby won a $125,000
contract from the General Services Administration in Fort Worth,
Texas, for cleaning supplies.
</P>
<P>
   Herley-Vegas Systems of Lancaster won a $436,750 contract from
the Navy in China Lake, Calif., for aircraft components.
</P>
<P>
   Valley Quarries Inc. of Chambersburg won a $169,584 contract
from the Army in Chambersburg for construction materials.
</P>
<P>
   Lenox Instrument Company Incorporated of Trevose won a $181,890
contract from the Army at Redstone Arsenal in Alabama for
laboratory equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Leica Microsystems Inc. of Exton won a $249,700 contract from
the Dept. of Veterans Affairs of San Francisco for laboratory
equipment.
</P>
<P>
   Pak Rapid Incorporated of Conshohocken won a $53,395 contract
