<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Rolling Stones add a seventh live album
 &HT;    By Russ Devault
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Few acts have the audacity, the sales strength or even the
longevity to release seven live albums, but ``No Security,'' due
Nov. 3 from Virgin, is the latest Rolling Stones live album.
</P>
<P>
   Recorded during the ``Bridges To Babylon'' tour, the release has
13 tracks, including strong takes of ``Memory Motel,'' ``Sister
Morphine'' and ``Gimme Shelter.''
</P>
<P>
   NEW IN STORES
</P>
<P>
   _ Bryan Adams, ``On A Day Like Today'' (A&AMP;M).
</P>
<P>
   _ Bizzy Bone, ``Heaven'z Movie'' (Mo Thugs/Ruthless/Relativity).
Grade: C.
</P>
<P>
   _ Elvis Costello &AMP; Burt Bacharach, ``Painted From Memory''
(Mercury). Grade: B.
</P>
<P>
   _ Bob Dylan, ``Bob Dylan Live 1966 'Royal Albert Hall'
Concert,'' (Columbia). Grade: A.
</P>
<P>
   _ Bruce Hornsby, ``Spirit Trail'' (RCA). Funky free-form piano
shines on 2-CD set from post-Grateful Dead Furthur Festival
mainstay.
</P>
<P>
   _ Kiss, ``Psycho Circus'' (Mercury). Grade: A-.
</P>
<P>
   Russ DeValt writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
