   CLINTON-EDUCATION (Washington) _ As budget bargaining
intensifies between the White House and Congress, President Clinton
visits an overcrowded public school with students in classroom
trailers. He seeks to dramatize his contention that the fiscal 1999
budget must include money for new classrooms. We examine rival
education plans offered by Republicans and Democrats. By STEWART M.
POWELL.
