<P>
   SCI-NOBEL-PHYSICS-CHEMISTRY (Undated) _ Nobel prizes in physics
and chemistry were bestowed Tuesday on five professors in the
United States, recognizing their discoveries since the 1960s that
led to far-reaching applications of quantum theory. The physics
prize, $978,000, will be shared by three Americans, whose work
sheds light on the cosmological structure of spacetime. The
chemistry prize, also $978,000, will be shared by two professors
whose work in quantum chemistry has made it easier for chemists and
pharmacologists to design molecules and predict their behavior
before the molecules exist. By Malcolm Browne.
</P>
<P>
   SCI-AUTOPSIES (Undated) _ Autopsies are on the decline in
frequency and accuracy, researchers report in the journal Nature.
By Lawrence K. Altman.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; DINING &LR;  (``d'' code)
</P>
