obscurity, freshman Democrat Rep. James H. Maloney has become a bit
of a national media star. While he points to his work on the
National Security Committee and the passage of his bill to put cops
in schools as the defining moments of his short career, the focus
has turned to Maloney's decision last week to join 31 other
Democrats in voting for the Republican impeachment resolution.
