   OHIO -- STEEL-NEY. Calling it a ``watered-down'' solution to a
devastating problem for American workers, Rep. Bob Ney, R-St.
Clairsville, voted against a resolution Monday night that urged the
President to respond to the surge of steel imports in the United
States as a result of the financial crises in Russia and Asia.
Foreign steel that can't be sold in these financially crippled
regions is getting dumped here, hurting U.S. steel companies. The
resolution, which failed 153-249, would have requested the
President to set up a committee to analyze the problems. Hurt
</P>
