Hispanic Caucus outline their top legislative priorities as the
105th Congress inches toward an expected close at the end of this
week. By JUDY HOLLAND.
</P>
<P>
   EDUCATION-COMPUTERS (Washington) _ Computers in schools are
helping students perform better in the classroom, according to a
new survey of teachers, principals and superintendents. Respondents
also say schools need to do more to get teachers trained in how to
teach computer skills and that a troubling ``digital divide''
exists between higher-income students who have computers at home
and lower-income students who don't. By DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
<P>
   CONGRESS-BUDGET (Washington) _ Republican leaders in Congress
say they are confident they are zeroing in on a budget agreement
that is palatable to the White House. By GREG McDONALD.
</P>
<P>
   U.S.-KOSOVO (Washington) _ President Clinton expresses
confidence that a team of international monitors will be able to
assess whether Serbian strongman Slobodan Milosevic has halted the
attacks in the Kosovo region of Yugoslavia. But officials have
still not ruled out possible military action to punish police
action in Kosovo. By NANCY MATHIS.
</P>
