Diego Padres. After seeing everything go their way while storming
to a 3-0 lead in the NL Championship Series, the Padres have now
watched almost every move backfire in the past two games against
the Atlanta Braves. Now the Padres face the daunting task of trying
to beat either Tom Glavine or Greg Maddux to claim the NL pennant,
and they will have to do it with a suddenly mortal Kevin Brown. By
CARLTON THOMPSON.
