HORROR-THEATER (Los Angeles) _ For the past few years Clive Barker
had been uncomfortable being seen as the ``horror guy,'' who is
invited out at Halloween to comment on the Dark Side. the man who
created Pinhead, the minion of evil with a bloodlust for human
souls from the ``Hellraiser'' movies, has turned his talents to
creating a maze for Universal Studios Hollywood to give fright fans
their ``own private piece of horror theater.'' By Rob Lowman. 
. 
UNIVERSAL-HORROR (Los Angeles) _ Universal Studios, which was once
the fright king with films such as ``Frankenstein'' and
``Dracula,'' wants to reclaim the role as leader in horror. By Rob
Lowman. 
 
 
TALKING-RADIO (Los Angeles) _ A Glendale community college student
was awarded a record-breaking $1,000,102.70 by KIIS-FM morning
personality Rick Dees after claiming the winning birthdate in a
call-in contest. By Fred Shuster. 

