<HEADLINE>
HEAVENLY MESSAGES WAFTING DOWN
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   A survey taken by DiMassimo Brand Advertising found that fans of
the TV show ``Touched by an Angel'' were less likely than fans of
all other shows to be fans of Bill Clinton; among the shows with
viewers most likely to approve of the president are ``Melrose
Place'' (about sex and 20-somethings) and ``Dawson's Creek'' (about
sex and teenagers).
</P>
<P>
   _ Vehicular metaphysics: Driving on 10th Street in San
Francisco,  &UR; Marvin Trapnell &LR;  saw a car bearing a bumper sticker
that read ``Advertising Is a Lie!'' driving by a Heineken billboard
that said ``Seek the Truth.'' And in Lynchburg, Va.,
 &UR; Betsy Nolan &LR;  was intrigued by the large ``GOD'' on the side of a
truck, for ``guaranteed overnight delivery.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Meanwhile,  &UR; Marc Capobiano &LR;  can't understand criticism of the
pope's making a saint of a woman born Jewish. ``This is a religion
whose God was born a Jew,'' he notes. ``Next to that, sainthood
seems almost trivial.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Upward bound: Street lore has it that shoes draped over
telephone wires indicate the neighborhood is open to drug
trafficking. So  &UR; Jane Mazarella  &LR; wants to know if there's any
meaning in the pair of boots that have been hanging on the branches
of a tree outside San Francisco's Pacific-Union Club atop Nob Hill
for months?
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; A FAKE PRO KNOWS THE SCORE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Outside the theater at the opening of the Irish play ``A Night
in November'' in New York,  &UR; Kevin Costner &LR; , who played a catcher in
``Bull Durham,'' made baseball small talk.
</P>
<P>
   ``When I first saw McGwire hit,'' he told  &UR; Baird Jones &LR; , ``I was
shocked, because it looked every time like he wasn't ready for the
pitch. So maybe that is his secret.'' This analysis fails to
explain how the late start functions as his ``secret.'' If baseball
is poetry, maybe Costner is an actor playing &UR; T.S. &LR; 
 &UR; Eliot &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Shoshanna Lonstein &LR; , whose fame stems solely from the fact
that she used to be  &UR; Jerry Seinfeld &LR; 's girlfriend, has designed her
own line of lingerie. ``I've always been obsessed with underwear,''
she told Cosmo. ``That's my favorite outfit.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Traude Buckland &LR;  was awed by the news in an Animal Protection
Institute newsletter that henceforth, the underside of Yoplait
yogurt containers will carry the message: ``Protect Wildlife: Crush
Before Disposal.'' This self-proclaimed ``wildlife-friendly''
notice _ attention, all consumers who study the undersides of
containers! _ is the solution dreamed up by Yoplait-maker General
Mills to the problem of animals getting their snouts stuck in
plastic containers with narrow tops.
</P>
<P>
   _ A lock of  &UR; King Louis XVI &LR; 's hair, harvested just after he was
beheaded, sold for $5,536 at an auction in Grenoble, France.
</P>
<P>
   _ Tired of the same old top 10 lists? The latest issue of Elle
Decor offers ``The 10 Most Exciting Ottomans.''
</P>
<P>
   _ If  &UR; Maureen Dowd &LR;  and  &UR; Michael Douglas  &LR; seemed an odd combo,
imagine this:  &UR; Christopher Buckley &LR;  told Mirabella magazine that
New York Times book reviewer  &UR; Michiko Kakutani &LR;  had dated  &UR; Paul &LR; 
 &UR; Simon &LR; , whose publicist confirms them as ``very close friends.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Actor  &UR; Derek Jacobi,  &LR; who plays the British painter  &UR; Francis &LR; 
 &UR; Bacon &LR;  in the forthcoming movie ``Love Is the Devil,'' told
Interview magazine how writer-director  &UR; John Maybury &LR;  dealt with
the estate not allowing Bacon's paintings to be shown in the movie.
``At the beginning, that might have been an obstacle,'' said
Jacobi, but Maybury ``made the artistic choice to try to make the
film itself look like and feel like a Bacon painting.
</P>
<P>
   ``So every shot, each frame, each setup was consciously created
and lit. We were placed in positions that suggested Bacon's
paintings.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Going back to Italy has been my dream since the day I came
home from there. ... It will be our greatest challenge _ a
psychological one. ... I think we may have a chance to bring back a
little of what has been lacking.''
</P>
<P>
   _ &LR;   &LR; Howard Schultz, CEO of Starbucks, telling the New Yorker
about the coffee chain's plans to conquer Italy.
</P>
</TEXT>
