c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Do you know what it's like to have your daughter come home and
say, `Mom, the kids say my clothes are tacky,' and then walk off
with her head hanging low?''
</P>
<P>
   _VERONICA WILLIAMS, who lives in a trailer park in Dixon, Ill.
</P>
