<HEADLINE>
TWO JC TRANSFERS SPARKING OREGON
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The Pac-10's top-ranked offense will be on display
Saturday at the Rose Bowl and it won't be wearing blue and gold.
</P>
<P>
   Oregon has averaged 539.8 yards and 50.6 points per game while
ascending to No. 11 in the rankings, thanks to superb play from two
junior college transfers, quarterback Akili Smith and tailback
Reuben Droughns.
</P>
<P>
   Smith, in his second year after transferring from Grossmont
(Calif.) Junior College, leads the nation in passing efficiency
(196.3), with 15 touchdowns and three interceptions. His
improvement is comparable to the strides Cade McNown made between
his sophomore and junior seasons.
</P>
<P>
   ``Almost every JC athlete takes a while to figure out the tempo
and speed of the Pac-10,'' Ducks coach Mike Bellotti said. ``Akili
is a perfect example. He spent the offseason figuring out what he
didn't know ... and now he's very comfortable in the offense.''
</P>
<P>
   Droughns didn't take as long to adjust. He leads the Pac-10 in
rushing (163 yards per game) and is the ninth player in conference
history to rush for 200 yards in three games.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's got to be the best back we've played,'' said Washington
State coach Mike Price, who faced UCLA's tailbacks two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
   __ Tear-jerker: Four days later, the Bruins are talking about
their emotional team meeting Friday night in which coach Bob Toledo
singled out his defensive line and quarterback, among others.
</P>
<P>
   ``He called them up and challenged each one of them,'' offensive
tackle Kris Farris said. ``He said, `Travor Turner, how many sacks
do you have? None. What are you going to do to change that? Pete
Holland, how many sacks do you have? None. What are you going to do
to change that?'
</P>
<P>
   ``Then he read from a stack of papers from Arizona that said our
quarterback wasn't worth a darn. He looked at Cade and said,
`They're challenging you, Cade. What are you going to do about it?'
Same with the offensive line. Same with the defensive backs.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was one hour of pure emotion, and when it ended we had no
doubt we'd beat them.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Name game: Toledo has unofficially christened the UCLA-Miami
game the ``Hurricane Bowl'' _ referring not to Miami's nickname but
to Hurricane Georges, which forced the cancellation of the Sept. 26
matchup.
</P>
<P>
   __ Where's Beano?: ESPN's ``College GameDay,'' with Chris
Fowler, Lee Corso and Kirk Herbstreit, will broadcast live outside
the Rose Bowl at 8 a.m. Saturday. It's the show's first-ever West
Coast appearance.
</P>
<P>
   __ By the numbers: UCLA is 4-0 for the first time since 1988,
when it started 7-0 and climbed to No. 1 in both polls.
</P>
<P>
   UCLA's 14-game winning streak is the nation's longest.
</P>
<P>
   The Bruins have scored on 21 of 24 trips inside the red zone
(20-yard line and in). That includes 20 touchdowns: 15 rushing,
five passing.
</P>
<P>
   UCLA's turnover margin (plus-1.5) is second in the Pac-10 and
11th in the nation.
</P>
<P>
   In Toledo's 2{ seasons, the Bruins are 11-0 when they score at
least 40 points.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
