New York Times Photo Package, moving 10/13/98. Photo clients will
automatically receive these photos via AP's PhotoExpress or may
download them from either the Wieck Photo Database in Dallas at
972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at 305-448-8411.
Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling (888) 603-1036
or 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT30) PARIS -- Oct. 13, 1998 -- PARIS-FASHION, 10-13 -- The
only vision more disturbing than the Goth panorama that Olivier
Theyskens displayed in his spectacular show Monday was the
suggestion of the return of wasp waists and full skirts a la Dior.
From left, Pleated olive top and military-inspired trousers by John
Galliano; White poncho and hot pants by Marc Jacobs for Louis
Vuitton; Theyskens's Goth leather jacket. (Dan Lecca/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT29) NEW YORK -- Oct. 13, 1998 -- BANKAMERICA-HEDGE, 10-13 --
David Shaw, founder of the D.E. Shaw hedge fund, in the trading
room. BankAmerica Corp., the nation's fifth-largest bank, is
expected to announce a big hedge fund loss Wednesday in the latest
example of the dangers posed to financial companies from the risky,
sometimes high-flying investment pools. Some experts say that
BankAmerica's overall exposure to the Shaw fund could be as large
as $1 billion. (Ozier Muhammad/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT28) MONTREAL -- Oct. 13, 1998 -- CANADA-BANKS, 10-13 -- John
Cleghorn, the chairman of the Royal Bank of Canada, wants to merge
with the Bank of Montreal in order to compete with giant foreign
institutions. ``If you're going to play in the big leagues, you've
got to be equipped,'' says Cleghorn, 57, who turned down a chance
to play for a professional Canadian football team. (Christopher
Morris/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT27) SILVER SPRING, Md. -- Oct. 13, 1998 -- CONGRESS-SPEND-2,
